description.et:
Seminarides osalemine ja kirjalikud seminari tekstide küsimuste vastused 20%
E -   vastused  üldjoontes loogilised, ent seosed puudulikud;
D -   vastused küsimustele üldjoontes loogilised ja seostatud; esineb probleeme materjali mõistmisel
C -  vastuste analüütilised seosed ja tõlgendused korralikud; 
B -  maht ja seostamine omandatud materjaliga väga hea, seoste ja viidete põhjalik analüüs, tõlgendamine julge ja seostele tuginev; 
A -  vastuse maht ja seostamine tekstiga loominguline, analüüsi sügavus ja iseseisva tõlgendamise tase silmapaistev, seosed põhjalikud ja leidlikud, lisatud omapoolne probleemi edasiarendus.

Participation in seminars and written answers to the questions about text (given by lecturer) 20%  
E -   answers are generally logical, but relations between different statements are missing;
D -   answers are generally logical and related each other; but there is still missing the demonstration of understanding of whole topic; 
C - analytical relations between topics and correct and interpretations are logical;   
B -  the scope of acquired material is very good and a student demonstrates the integration of new concepts with his/her previous knowledge, analysis of different viewpoints are courageous and thorough;
A -  the scope of acquired material is very good and a student demonstrates the integration of new concepts with his/her previous knowledge, relations between topics are thorough and inventive, there is also included a critical point of view and a problem solving.

Kirjalik eksam, mis hõlmab ka kohustusliku kirjanduse kontrolli,
moodustab 80 % hindest.
 Hindamiskriteeriumid:
	-   loengus ja seminarides omandatu maht;
	-	analüütilisus, seoste loomine, tõlgendamisoskus;
	-	teemakäsitluse loogilisus ja terviklikkus.

E -  analüüsi ja iseseisva tõlgendamise elemendid olemas, teemakäsitlus üldjoontes loogiline, ent seosed lünklikud;
D -  analüüs ja iseseisev tõlgendamine arusaadavad, ent ebakindlad, teemakäsitus üldjoontes loogiline ja seostatud;
C -  analüütilised seosed ja tõlgendused korralikud, kindlus seoste loomisel, teemakäsitlus loogiline, ent terviku seisukohalt täheldatavad mõned küsitavused;
B -  maht ja seostamine omandatud materjaliga väga hea, seoste ja viidete põhjalik analüüs, tõlgendamine julge ja seostele tuginev, teemakäsitus tervikuna loogiline ja ladus;
A -  maht ja seostamine tekstiga loominguline, analüüsi sügavus ja iseseisva tõlgendamise tase silmapaistev, seosed põhjalikud ja leidlikud, teemakäsitlus uudne, loogiline, tekst tervikuna väga hästi sõnastatud.

Written exam, which include also understanding seminar text, 80% of total mark

 Criteria of assessment:  
	-   acquired scope of  topics that are studied in lectures and seminars
	-   analytical skills, creating of relations between different topics, skills of interpretations;
	-   consistency and wholeness of topic.  

 E - the form is, in general, in compliance with the requirements and correct; references are minimal and insecure; the elements of analysis and independent interpreting are there; the coverage of the subject is, in general, logical, but the connections are full of gaps;
D - the form is in compliance with the requirements and, in general, correct; references are minimal, but relevant; the analysis and independent interpreting is understandable, but at times insecure; the coverage of the subject is logical and associated;
C - the form is in compliance with the requirements and correct; references are relevant and sufficient; analytical connections and interpretations are proper and there is certainty in creating connections; the treatment of the subject is logical, but there are some weaknesses from the point of view of the whole;
B - the form is excellent; the choice, amount and association of references with the text is very good; thorough analysis of connections and references; bold interpretation based on connections; the treatment of the subject as a whole is logical and smooth;
A - the form is excellent; the choice, amount and association of references with the text is creative; the depth of the analysis and the level of independent interpretation is remarkable; the connections are thorough-going and creative; the treatment of the subject is innovative and logical; the text is a remarkable achievement on the whole.
